Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Chop @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into 1-inch cubes. Place potatoes and @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} in a large #pot of salted water. Bring to a boil and cook until very tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and return to same pot.

Meanwhile, trim @sugar snap peas{12%ounce}, then place on a #baking sheet and toss with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until just starting soften, about ~{10%minutes}.

While snap peas roast, heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Season @boneless pork chops{24%ounce} all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}. Add to pan and sear until browned, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Transfer to baking sheet with snap peas and roast together until pork is cooked through and snap peas are tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Halve and remove cores from @apple{2}(chopped into ½-inch cubes), then chop into ½-inch cubes. Heat @butter{2%tbsp} and a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium heat. Add apples and cook until golden, ~{5-7%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and 1 cup water. Increase heat to medium-high and cook until apples are tender and sauce is thick, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @butter{2%tbsp} to #pot with potatoes and cauliflower and toss to melt.

> If potatoes and cauliflower have cooled, reheat briefly over low heat.

Mash with a #fork or #potato masher{} until mostly smooth. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide cauliflower mash between plates. Top with pork and snap peas. Drizzle with apple pan sauce, making sure to spoon any chunks of apple onto plate.